ent at lehman brothers in new york and prior to that a managing director of abn amro in london where he joined from sbc warburg within the ma groups of lehman brothers abn amro and sbc warburg he advised a variety of clients with a specialization in the financial institutions sector he has extensive experience working in a number of latin american countries including advising on privatizations and acting for european companies on crossborder transactions in the region anderson began his career with the economist group in london originally as a journalist before becoming senior latin american economistafter studying economics in lima mr anderson obtained a msc in economics at birkbeck college a phd abd in economic history at the london school of economics and a diploma in macroeconomic policy management at the harvard institute of international development portfolio analyst denis colevice president portfolio analyst mr cole has  years of industry experience at gramercy mr cole works with the emerging markets debt portfolio managers where he assists with modeling investment ideas performing quantitative portfolio analytics and supports the monitoring of portfolio holdings to identify securities that may be sell candidates additionally he works with both the sales and investor relations teams to aid in the preparation of marketing materials including pitch presentations ad hoc requests and prospecting prior to joining gramercy mr cole was employed by nexar capital group he worked within nexar capital’s volatility hedge fund group including a volatility arbitrage hedge fund and a variety of short biased hedge funds there he concentrated on creating portfolio exposure attribution and risk analysis reports drafting monthend client commentaries and identifyingprospecting potential investors in addition he was active in supporting trading activities by executing trades entering data into trade blotters and creating models to back test delta hedging strategies prior to that 